1. On je *lažov*. (He is a liar.)
2. Ne slušaj šta ti priča, on je *lažov*. (Don't listen to what he says, he's a liar.)
3. On je uhvaćen u laži, tako da sada znamo da je *lažov*. (He was caught in a lie, so now we know he's a liar.)
4. Ne verujem mu, jer mi se čini da je *lažov*. (I don't trust him, because I think he's a liar.)
5. Ne možeš mu verovati, on je poznati *lažov*. (You can't trust him, he's a well-known liar.)
6. Kako se usuđuješ da mi lažeš? Zar nisi svestan da sam ja već prozreo da si *lažov*? (How dare you lie to me? Aren't you aware that I've already figured out that you're a liar?)
7. Ona je lako nasela na njegove laži, ali sada zna da je on *lažov*. (She easily fell for his lies, but now she knows he's a liar.)
8. On stalno laže da bi izbegao odgovornost, tako da je postao poznat kao veliki *lažov*. (He constantly lies to avoid responsibility, so he has become known as a big liar.)
9. Nemoj da veruješ njegovim lažima, on je običan *lažov*. (Don't believe his lies, he's just a plain liar.)
10. Sve njegove tvrdnje su se pokazale kao laži, tako da nema sumnje da je on pravi *lažov*. (All his claims turned out to be lies, so there's no doubt he's a real liar.)